HLS 26RS-5344 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 339
BY REPRESENTATIVE TAYLOR
CLERKS OF COURT: Requests the Louisiana State Law Institute to conduct a statewide
study of clerk of court procedures
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To urge and request the Louisiana State Law Institute to study clerk of court procedures
3 throughout the state and to report its findings and any recommendations for uniform
4 court procedures to the House of Representatives prior to the convening of the 2027
5 Regular Session of the Legislature of Louisiana.
6 WHEREAS, there are forty-one judicial districts in the state as well as the district
7 court in Orleans Parish; and
8 WHEREAS, each judicial district court and the district court in Orleans Parish have
9 a clerk of court with individual rules and procedures for litigants and persons interacting
10 within respective offices; and
11 WHEREAS, a uniform system of rules and procedures does not exist for the clerks
12 of court in this state; and
13 WHEREAS, efficient interaction with the courts by our citizens will lead to a more
14 fair and equitable justice system; and
15 WHEREAS, the Louisiana State Law Institute has the duty "to promote and
16 encourage the clarification and simplification of the law of Louisiana and its better
17 adaptation to present social needs; to secure the better administration of justice and to carry
18 on scholarly legal research and scientific legal work."
19 THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
20 Legislature of Louisiana does hereby urge and request the Louisiana State Law Institute to
21 study clerk of court procedures throughout the state and to report its findings and any
